cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the communication reliability and latency in a heterogeneous network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of radio resources and densities of users and access points, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a proactive multi-cell association scheme to improve communication reliability, which involves control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the uplink and downlink delays, which are important factors in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed scheme may have implications for security and cryptography in wireless networks.
